# URL Handling: Web, PWA & Electron

The app runs on three platforms with different URL behaviors:

| Platform | Origin | API calls | Static assets | Server media |
|----------|--------|-----------|---------------|--------------|
| **Web/PWA** | Same as server | Relative (`/api/...`) | Absolute (`/assets/...`) | Relative (`/api/uploads/...`) |
| **Electron** | `app://jablu` | Proxied by protocol handler | Served locally by protocol handler | Proxied by protocol handler |

## Key Rules

### 1. Never hardcode absolute paths for public assets in components
Use `import.meta.env.BASE_URL` to prefix public directory assets:

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — breaks in Electron (file:// or app:// origin)
<img src="/favicon.svg" />

// ✅ GOOD — resolves to "/" on web, "./" on Electron build
<img src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}favicon.svg`} />
```

### 2. Keep `api.baseUrl` empty in Electron
The `app://` protocol handler proxies `/api/` and `/uploads/` to the server. Never set `api.baseUrl` in Electron — all API paths stay relative.

### 3. Use `resolveMediaUrl()` for server-provided media URLs
Avatars, attachments, and icons from the API are paths like `/api/uploads/...`. Wrap them with `resolveMediaUrl()` from `@/lib/api`:

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — won't resolve to server in Electron if baseUrl fallback needed
<img src={user.avatarUrl} />

// ✅ GOOD
<img src={resolveMediaUrl(user.avatarUrl)} />
```

### 4. WebSocket connects directly to the server
The protocol handler cannot proxy WebSockets. Socket.io reads the server URL from `getStoredServerUrl()` in Electron, and uses same-origin on web.

### 5. Electron builds require `ELECTRON=1` env var
This sets `base: "./"` in Vite so asset paths are relative. Without it, paths like `/assets/index.js` break on `file://` or `app://`.

```bash
# Web build (default base: "/")
pnpm --filter @chat/web build

# Electron build (base: "./")
ELECTRON=1 pnpm --filter @chat/web build
```

### 6. MIME types in protocol handler
When adding new static asset types to the web app, also add their MIME type to `MIME_TYPES` in `apps/desktop/src/main/index.ts`. Missing entries cause silent load failures (e.g., `.mjs`, `.wasm`).

### 7. External links in PWA
Always use `target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"` on links to external URLs. Without this, iOS PWA navigates away from the app entirely.
